# Code owners for open-bridge.
#
# GitHub auto-requests a review from the listed owner(s) on any pull request
# that touches a matching path. Combined with branch protection on `main`
# (required pull-request review), this means nothing merges without a
# maintainer's approval — the floor for the manual-then-AI-assisted merge
# process described in the project's contribution workflow.
#
# Until a maintainer team exists, the project lead owns everything. To move to
# team-based ownership later, replace @mboiman with a team handle such as
# @bks-lab/maintainers — CODEOWNERS lines accept teams and users alike.

# Default owner for the whole repository.
*                       @mboiman

# Extra-sensitive areas. Redundant while a single owner holds `*`, kept
# explicit so they survive a future team split (legal/CI/leak-gate must always
# stay lead-reviewed).
/LICENSE                @mboiman
/TRADEMARK.md           @mboiman
/AUTHORS                @mboiman
/.github/               @mboiman
/scripts/               @mboiman
